{
  "stem": "1216.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, in one of my first letters to [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], I asked them that they have my family and me, and Hans' family and him, in their cards.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they wrote back and said, yes, they had us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And by the way, that family was with such and such transport, on such and such a date, transported to Auschwitz and gassed on arrival.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was just like a-- like somebody had hit me over the head with a stone block.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because it came totally unexpectedly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had never thought that I would ever find out what happened to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it's hard to believe even now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] As we all have, I think, fantasies, when you don't know what happened to somebody, that maybe you'll meet them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I still think that about Hans, even though I know up there with my brain that no, can't be, because he's dead.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But he isn't really dead, not to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So then that was in October '44, as I now know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And after that, I was mostly by myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes and no to both.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I don't remember seeing anything, either because I actually didn't see it, or because it's all gone blank.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know which.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, yes, violence was done.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When the Nazis came by, as they very often did, through the streets, if you didn't go out of the way soon enough, or you didn't stand at attention well enough, or whatever, at least for the adult, they were just as likely as not to either slap you or whip you, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I do not remember seeing it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
